Problem 2

You can also embed plots, for example:

set.seed(1)

plot_df = tibble(
  x = rnorm(500),
  y = rnorm(500),
  vec_logical = (x + y)> 0,
  vec_numberic = c(as.numeric(vec_logical)),
  vec_factor = c(as.factor(vec_numberic))
)

# color points using logical variables
p1 <- ggplot(plot_df, aes (x = x, y = y, color = vec_logical)) + geom_point()
p1

# color points using numberic variables
ggplot(plot_df, aes (x = x, y = y, color = vec_numberic)) + geom_point()

# color points using factor variables
ggplot(plot_df, aes (x = x, y = y, color = vec_factor)) + geom_point()

# export scatterplot by ggsave


ggsave(filename = "hw1_problem2_plot", plot = p1,
    device = "pdf", path = NULL,
    scale = 1)
## Saving 7 x 5 in image

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
